      <scopecontent id="aspace_4f3e55b163b969fbd9719aff1976662d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of legal papers and other materials from the firm of Cheadle, Thompson &amp; Haysom of Port Elizabeth, South Africa. The firm represented Dr. Wendy Orr and forty-two other applicants in obtaining an interim restraining order from the Port Elizabeth Supreme Court against the South African police in September 1985. Dr. Orr, as district surgeon, charged that detainees held under the country's state of emergency decree in Port Elizabeth and Uitenhage were brutally assaulted on a massive scale by the police.</p>
         <p>The bulk of the collection consists of the affidavits of the applicants. Supplementary material includes printed matter pertaining to other instances of excessive police force, legal challenges to the state of emergency measures, legal aspects of apartheid, and groups protesting detention policies in South Africa.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
